This series also span a second new ongoing series, The Uncanny Inhumans. The series also had an Inhuman Special one-shot.

description:
Ongoing series about a guy called Sam Whistler who wakes up in a hotel room with his hands bandaged and no memory about who he is and how he got there. Despite everything around him looking familiar he can't make any connection. Even worse, some angry mob is banging at the door. Sam has to stay clear of his pursuers... and find out his identity.

Dead Letters is written by Christopher Sebela (High Crimes, Ghost) with illustrations from Chris Visions.

deck: KATUSHA, GIRL SOLDIER OF THE GREAT PATRIOTIC WAR is a coming-of-age story told against the backdrop of the bloodiest conflict in human history: the 1941-1945 Eastern Front between Nazi Germany and Soviet Russia. Created by writer/artist Wayne Vansant (Marvel's THE NAM), KATUSHA is a graphic novel series inspired by the experiences of thousands of women who served in the Red Army as pilots, snipers, tank drivers, and other roles. It tells the story of a Ukrainian farm girl who because a tank commander.
name: Katusha Girl Soldier of the Great Patriotic War
